(A Reproducible Pipeline for Streaming Log Analytics at Scale) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Authors: Ravi Kumar; Anna Fischer) Tj
T* (Affiliations: Indian Institute of Technology Delhi / Technical University of Munich) Tj
T* (Correspondence: rkumar@example.org) Tj
T* (Document: Typeset galley \(published version\)) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Abstract) Tj
T* (Operational logs are a primary signal for diagnosing distributed systems, yet pipelines that) Tj
T* (process them are often ad hoc and hard to reproduce.) Tj
T* (We present a modular pipeline that combines schema-on-read ingestion with incremental) Tj
T* (aggregation, and evaluate it on three public workloads.) Tj
T* (Results indicate consistent latency under sustained load and a clear path to horizontal) Tj
T* (scaling.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Keywords: stream processing, observability, reproducibility, distributed systems) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. Introduction) Tj
T* (This manuscript is part of a realistic but synthetic Open Journal Systems instance used for) Tj
T* (non-production testing. The content is fictional; any resemblance to real studies is) Tj
T* (coincidental.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (2. Methods) Tj
T* (The study design, materials, and analysis described here are illustrative placeholders that) Tj
T* (mirror the structure of a genuine research article so that downstream tooling sees plausible) Tj
T* (inputs.) Tj
